<span class="taxonomyterm18916feed">NVRA instructions Idaho English</span>


            <p><strong>State Instructions —&nbsp;IDAHO</strong></p>

<p><strong>Updated: 06-27-2022</strong></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Registration Deadline</strong> — 25 days before the election.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>6. ID Number.</strong> Enter the number from your Idaho driver's license card or state identification card issued by the Idaho Transportation Department. If you have no such card, enter the last 4 digits of your social security number.</p>

<p><strong>7. Choice of Party.</strong> Unless the political party chooses to have an open primary, affiliating with a political party is required if you wish to participate in a party's primary election.&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>8. Race or Ethnic Group.</strong> Leave blank.</p>

<p><strong>9. Signature.</strong> To register in Idaho you must:</p>

<ul>
	<li>be a citizen of the United States</li>
	<li>have resided in Idaho and in the county for 30 days prior to the day of election</li>
	<li>be at least 18 years old</li>
	<li>not have been convicted of a felony, and without having been restored to the rights of citizenship, or confined in prison on conviction of a criminal offense</li>
</ul>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Mailing Address:</strong></p>

<p>Secretary of State</p>

<p>P.O. Box 83720</p>

<p>State Capitol Bldg.</p>

<p>Boise, ID 83720-0080</p>

      
